Q_DESC:
Given a matrix of size NxM where every element is either O or X, replace O with X if surrounded by X. A O (or a set of O) is considered to be by surrounded by X if there are X at locations just below, just above, just left and just right of it.                                        Examples:

Input: mat[N][M] =  {{'X', 'O', 'X', 'X', 'X', 'X'},
                     {'X', 'O', 'X', 'X', 'O', 'X'},
                     {'X', 'X', 'X', 'O', 'O', 'X'},
                     {'O', 'X', 'X', 'X', 'X', 'X'},
                     {'X', 'X', 'X', 'O', 'X', 'O'},
                     {'O', 'O', 'X', 'O', 'O', 'O'},
                    };
Output: mat[N][M] =  {{'X', 'O', 'X', 'X', 'X', 'X'},
                      {'X', 'O', 'X', 'X', 'X', 'X'},
                      {'X', 'X', 'X', 'X', 'X', 'X'},
                      {'O', 'X', 'X', 'X', 'X', 'X'},
                      {'X', 'X', 'X', 'O', 'X', 'O'},
                      {'O', 'O', 'X', 'O', 'O', 'O'},
                    };

Input: mat[N][M] =  {{'X', 'X', 'X', 'X'}
                     {'X', 'O', 'X', 'X'}
                     {'X', 'O', 'O', 'X'}
                     {'X', 'O', 'X', 'X'}
                     {'X', 'X', 'O', 'O'}
                    };
Input: mat[N][M] =  {{'X', 'X', 'X', 'X'}
                     {'X', 'X', 'X', 'X'}
                     {'X', 'X', 'X', 'X'}
                     {'X', 'X', 'X', 'X'}
                     {'X', 'X', 'O', 'O'}
                    };

Input:
The first line of input contains an integer T denoting the no of test cases. Then T test cases follow. The first line of each test case contains two integers N and M denoting the size of the matrix. Then in the next line are N*M space separated values of the matrix.

Output:
For each test case print the space separated values of the new matrix.

Constraints:
1=T=10
1=mat[][]=100
1=n,m=20
